sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1720
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was designed for a class and does not really exist. It is comprised of the part BBa_M1718, which is a combination of Optimized hepcidin and spider silk, and 5 repeats of the part BBa_K844004.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part comes from the AA sequence for hepcidin, but has been optimized for E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimized for E. coli using NCBI OPTIMIZER.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1718
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is for a class project and does not really exist. The part combines the part BBa_M1716 that codes for the E. coli optimized hepcidin protein with part BBa_K844004, which codes for a single coding region of spider silk protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Decker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Both protein coding regions are based on original AA sequences, but have been optimized for expression in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk 1x Subunit "B" (Balanced tRNA codon optimized)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Spider silk subunit optimized to use a more balanced, but still greatly reduced, number of tRNA codons; contains two elasticity domains and one strength domain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrea Halling
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Artificially designed based on BBa_K844002 and DNA was synthesized
